news.article_text:
This article first appeared on GuruFocus.

U.S. stocks fell Monday as a risk-off mood swept markets, with tech leading the decline.

The Nasdaq Composite was down about 0.6%, the S&P 500 was down about 0.4% and the Dow Jones Industrial Average slid about 0.5%, reflecting broad pressure across benchmarks.

Most of the "Magnificent Seven" pulled back, led by drops of around 1% in Nvidia (NASDAQ:NVDA), Meta (NASDAQ:META) and Tesla (NASDAQ:TSLA), while Amazon (AMZN) bucked the trend and held gains.

news.headline: Today's Market: Nasdaq Leads Market Retreat. Nvidia, Meta, Tesla Slide Amid Risk-Off Mood
news.summary: U.S. stocks fell Monday as a risk-off mood swept markets, with tech leading the decline. Bitcoin (BTC-USD) plunged nearly 6% to around $84,000, and crypto-linked names were hit hard.
news.article_text:
This article first appeared on GuruFocus.

U.S. stocks fell Monday as a risk-off mood swept markets, with tech leading the decline.

The Nasdaq Composite was down about 0.6%, the S&P 500 was down about 0.4% and the Dow Jones Industrial Average slid about 0.5%, reflecting broad pressure across benchmarks.

Most of the "Magnificent Seven" pulled back, led by drops of around 1% in Nvidia (NASDAQ:NVDA), Meta (NASDAQ:META) and Tesla (NASDAQ:TSLA), while Amazon (AMZN) bucked the trend and held gains.
